          "book": "John",
          "chapter": 3,
          "verses": [
            23
          ],
          "verse_count": 1,
          "testament": "NT",
          "raw": "John 3:23",
          "source": "EAS"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "(springs) a place “near to Salim,” at which John baptized. (John 3:23) It was evidently west of the Jordan, comp. (John 3:22) with John 3:26 and with John 1:28 And abounded in water. It is given in the Omomasticon as eight miles south of Scythopolis “near Salem and the Jordan.”",
